<paragraph id="035B075AFFF9FFC8FF23FE5F3996FE68" blockId="8.[151,1437,259,1221]" box="[199,1170,475,502]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Body (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF9FFC8FEF7FE5F3C52FE6B" box="[275,342,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[161,1436,533,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-159@2.[151,1436,525,1910]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Habitus 1 N. ingentis; 2 N. resimus; 3 N. leigongensis; 4 N. yujiei; 5 N. muricatus; 6 N. excertus; 7 N. serratus. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6554672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6554672/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) dark brown; legs reddish brown; antennae reddish brown to light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF9FFC8FF23FE7B3828FDA0" blockId="8.[151,1437,259,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Head (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF9FFC8FEF5FE7B3C66FD84" box="[273,354,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,753,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-250@7.[151,1436,741,1909]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28–32. Nazeris muricatus 28 forebody; 29 male sternite VII; 30 male sternite VIII; 31 aedeagus in ventral view; 32 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 28 1.0 mm; 29–32 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552229/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) 1.01–1.05 times as long as wide; punctation moderately dense and coarse, distinctly umbilicate, interstices lacking microsculpture; postocular portion approximately 1.8–2.0 times as long as eye length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF9FFC8FF23FDCC3E9CFD34" blockId="8.[151,1437,259,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF9FFC8FEA1FDC33C93FDFC" box="[325,407,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,753,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-250@7.[151,1436,741,1909]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28–32. Nazeris muricatus 28 forebody; 29 male sternite VII; 30 male sternite VIII; 31 aedeagus in ventral view; 32 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 28 1.0 mm; 29–32 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552229/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) 1.08–1.16 times as long as wide, 0.95–1.03 times as long and 0.90–0.93 times as broad as head; punctation non-umbilicate, moderately dense and as coarse as that of head; midline posteriorly with very short and narrow impunctate elevation; interstices lacking microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF9FFC8FF23FD373885FD6C" blockId="8.[151,1437,259,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF9FFC8FEFAFD373C76FD50" box="[286,370,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,753,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-250@7.[151,1436,741,1909]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28–32. Nazeris muricatus 28 forebody; 29 male sternite VII; 30 male sternite VIII; 31 aedeagus in ventral view; 32 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 28 1.0 mm; 29–32 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552229/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) 0.52–0.60 times as long as wide, 0.50–0.53 times as long and 0.97–1.03 times as broad as pronotum; punctation as dense as, and slightly coarser than that of pronotum; interstices lacking microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF9FFC8FF23FD7F396AFCA4" blockId="8.[151,1437,259,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Abdomen with punctation dense and rather coarse on tergites III–V, dense and less coarse on tergite VI, moderately dense and fine on tergites VII–VIII; with fine microsculpture on all tergites.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF9FFC8FF23FCC739B7FC57" blockId="8.[151,1437,259,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Male. Sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF9FFC8FE4EFCC73CFAFCC0" box="[426,510,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,753,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-250@7.[151,1436,741,1909]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28–32. Nazeris muricatus 28 forebody; 29 male sternite VII; 30 male sternite VIII; 31 aedeagus in ventral view; 32 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 28 1.0 mm; 29–32 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552229/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin truncate at middle. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF9FFC8FB77FCC739E3FCC0" box="[1171,1255,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,753,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-250@7.[151,1436,741,1909]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28–32. Nazeris muricatus 28 forebody; 29 male sternite VII; 30 male sternite VIII; 31 aedeagus in ventral view; 32 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 28 1.0 mm; 29–32 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552229/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) with V-shaped posterior excision. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF9FFC8FE17FCE33F7EFC1C" box="[499,634,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,753,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-250@7.[151,1436,741,1909]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28–32. Nazeris muricatus 28 forebody; 29 male sternite VII; 30 male sternite VIII; 31 aedeagus in ventral view; 32 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 28 1.0 mm; 29–32 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552229/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Figs 31, 32</figureCitation>
) moderately sclerotized; ventral process long, narrowed apicad, with acute apex in ventral view, curved ventrad in lateral view; dorso-lateral apophyses slender, distinctly curved in ventral view, slightly widened near apex in ventral view, not reaching apex of ventral process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4BFE54D1FFF9FFC8FF23FC573971FBE0" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF9FFC8FF23FC57390CFB8F" blockId="8.[151,1437,259,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF9FFC8FF23FC573F28FC70" bold="true" box="[199,556,979,1005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Distribution and habitat data.</emphasis>
The species is known from Leigong Mt. and Xiaodanjiang in eastern 
<collectingRegion id="C120C9B8FFF9FFC8FAD1FC57389DFC70" box="[1333,1433,979,1005]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
. The specimens were collected by sifting leaf litter at altitudes of 
<quantity id="C41CAABFFFF9FFC8FC89FC733900FB8F" box="[877,1028,1015,1042]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.425" metricValueMax="2.15" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" unit="m" value="1425.0" valueMax="2150.0" valueMin="700.0">700–2,150 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF9FFC8FF23FB9F3971FBE0" blockId="8.[151,1437,259,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF9FFC8FF23FB9F3CB6FBA8" bold="true" box="[199,434,1051,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
The new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C4E47CD9FFF9FFC8FCAFFB98394BFBA8" authority="Hu &amp; Qiao" authorityName="Hu &amp; Qiao" box="[843,1103,1051,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nazeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosus">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF9FFC8FCAFFB983EC3FBA8" box="[843,967,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">N. rugosus</emphasis>
Hu &amp; Qiao
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="67757AABFFF9FFC8FBBBFB9F385BFBA8" author="Hu, J. Y. &amp; Qiao, Y. J." box="[1119,1375,1051,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" pagination="431 - 441" refId="ref5879" refString="Hu, J. Y. &amp; Qiao, Y. J. (2019) Five new species of Nazeris Fauvel in Guangxi, China (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Paederinae). Zootaxa, 4543 (3), 431 - 441. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4543.3.8" type="journal article" year="2019">Hu &amp; Qiao 2019: 436</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF9FFC8FA88FB9F3DDAFBC4" captionStart-0="FIGURES 13–17" captionStart-1="FIGURES 18–22" captionStart-2="FIGURES 23–27" captionStartId-0="4.[151,264,1396,1420]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,264,1724,1748]" captionStartId-2="6.[151,264,1497,1521]" captionTargetBox-0="[153,1422,191,1362]" captionTargetBox-1="[155,1425,423,1692]" captionTargetBox-2="[159,1426,319,1465]" captionTargetId-0="figure-30@4.[151,1437,181,1372]" captionTargetId-1="figure-122@5.[151,1437,417,1701]" captionTargetId-2="figure-99@6.[151,1436,308,1473]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionTargetPageId-2="6" captionText-0="FIGURES 13–17. Nazeris resimus 13 forebody; 14 male sternite VII; 15 male sternite VIII; 16 aedeagus in ventral view; 17 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 13 1.0 mm; 14–17 0.5 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 18–22. Nazeris leigongensis 18 forebody; 19 male sternite VII; 20 male sternite VIII; 21 aedeagus in ventral view; 22 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 18 1.0 mm; 19–22 0.5 mm." captionText-2="FIGURES 23–27. Nazeris yujiei 23 forebody; 24 male sternite VII; 25 male sternite VIII; 26 aedeagus in ventral view; 27 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 23 1.0 mm; 24–27 0.5 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552151" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552155" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552225" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6552151/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6552155/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6552225/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Figs 17–24</figureCitation>
) in general appearance but can be separated by the microsculpture only present on abdomen, by the ventral process of aedeagus distinctly wider and lacking basal laminae in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF9FFC8FBF0FBE7396DFBE0" box="[1044,1129,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[152,1421,753,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-250@7.[151,1436,741,1909]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28–32. Nazeris muricatus 28 forebody; 29 male sternite VII; 30 male sternite VIII; 31 aedeagus in ventral view; 32 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 28 1.0 mm; 29–32 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552229/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4BFE54D1FFF9FFC8FF23FB033C01FB58" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF9FFC8FF23FB033C01FB58" blockId="8.[151,1437,259,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF9FFC8FF23FB033C4AFB3C" bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1185]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet (Latin, adjective: pointed) alludes to the pointed ventral process of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
